{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida9e8e8e1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2868"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2868"},"text":"§ 2868.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Utility services: furnishing for certain buildings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Appropriations for the Department of Defense may be used for utility services for buildings constructed at private cost, as authorized by law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida9e8e8e2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/370/s1/j/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–370, § 1(j)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-07-19"},"text":"July 19, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/848"},"text":"102 Stat. 848","children":[],"tail":", § 2490; renumbered § 2868, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/dA/tIII/s371/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, div. A, title III, § 371(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/1705"},"text":"111 Stat. 1705","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tVI/s651/e/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title VI, § 651(e)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1972"},"text":"118 Stat. 1972","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida9e8e8e3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"ida9e8e8e4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is based on ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/190/s101/b/tVIII/s8006/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–190, § 101(b) [title VIII, § 8006(b)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/1185"},"text":"99 Stat. 1185","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In two instances, the source section for provisions to be codified provides that defense appropriations may be used for “welfare and recreation” or “welfare and recreational” purposes. (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/212/s735"},"text":"Section 735 of Public Law 98–212","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/190/s8006/b"},"text":"section 8006(b) of Public Law 99–190","children":[],"tail":", to be codified as "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2241/a/1"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 2241(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":" and 2490(2), respectively). The committee added the term “morale” in both of these two instances to conform to the usual “MWR” usage for morale, welfare, and recreation activities."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida9e8e8e5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida9e8e8e6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":" substituted “for buildings constructed at private cost, as authorized by law.” for “for—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) buildings constructed at private cost, as authorized by law; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) buildings on military reservations authorized by regulation to be used for morale, welfare, and recreational purposes.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2490"},"text":"section 2490 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
